"media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819066?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">有关黑客工具使用日益增多的报道引发了限制其使用的呼声。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：布伦丹·麦克德米德/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001063162"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dustin-volz" itemprop="url" rel="author">达斯汀·沃尔兹</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 18 日上午 10:37 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/european-spyware-firms-threaten-global-security-and-privacy-u-s-says-ca86c35f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>华盛顿——拜登政府将两家新的外国科技公司列入其出口禁令名单，指责这些公司销售<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-restricts-use-of-commercial-hacking-tools-by-u-s-agencies-f0a4afda?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">网络入侵工具</a>，对数字隐私和安全构成全球威胁。</p><p>美国商务部表示，正在将在希腊和爱尔兰持有股份的 Intellexa 以及在匈牙利和北马其顿持有股份的 Cytrox 添加到其实体名单中，该名单通常禁止美国公司与它们进行贸易活动。</p><p>这是拜登政府试图围绕不断增长且利润丰厚的间谍软件行业制定规则的最新行动，该行业的公司向世界各地的执法和情报机构出售高性能数字监控工具，这些工具能够秘密渗透到目标智能手机和其他设备中。设备。美国官员表示，此类工具的扩散可能危害美国国家安全并侵犯人权。</p><p>美国商务部副部长唐·格雷夫斯表示：“这项规则重申了保护全世界人权是美国外交政策的一项基本利益。” “实体清单仍然是我们武器库中的一个强大工具，可以防止世界各地的不良行为者利用美国技术来实现他们的邪恶目标。”</p><p> Intellexa 没有立即回应置评请求。无法联系 Cytrox。</p><p>虽然数字入侵软件供应商表示，他们的工具对于追踪暴力犯罪分子和国家安全威胁至关重要，但西方政府和隐私倡导者表示，这些工具经常被威权政府和民主政府滥用，以针对记者、政治对手、人权倡导者和其他人不涉嫌有不当行为。</p><p>有关从以色列和其他地方的公司购买的黑客工具越来越多地使用的报道激起了欧洲和美国限制其使用的呼声。以色列科技公司 NSO Group 曾于 2021 年与其他三家供应商一起<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israeli-cyber-firm-nso-group-blacklisted-by-u-s-amid-phone-hacking-allegations-11635956794?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">被拜登政府列入黑名单</a>。据《华尔街日报》五月份报道，这一行动和公众的大量负面关注损害了 NSO 集团的业务，在贷款人强制改变控制权并计划继续其有争议的间谍软件业务后，该公司最近<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/israeli-cyber-company-nso-group-has-new-ownership-after-u-s-blacklist-a2cda00a" target="_blank" class="icon none">获得了新的所有权</a>。</p><p>今年早些时候，拜登总统发布了一项史无前例的行政命令， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-restricts-use-of-commercial-hacking-tools-by-u-s-agencies-f0a4afda?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">限制在联邦政府内部使用商业间谍软件</a>，但并没有完全禁止其使用，无论是用于攻击目的还是用于测试。当时，美国政府还透露，相信至少有 50 名在海外工作的美国人员受到此类间谍软件的攻击，这一数字远高于之前的估计。</p><p>多伦多大学公民实验室的网络安全研究人员此前已将 Cytrox 与名为 Predator 的监控软件联系起来，该软件能够通过 WhatsApp 发送的单击链接来感染 iPhone。研究小组在亚美尼亚、埃及、希腊、印度尼西亚和沙特阿拉伯等多个国家找到了 Predator 客户，并将该工具与针对埃及政治异见人士的黑客攻击联系起来。</p><p> Citizen Lab 还得出结论，Cytrox 是其所谓的“Intellexa 联盟”的一部分，该联盟是 2019 年左右成立的一组间谍软件供应商的总称。</p><p>周二的行动是在美国和几个盟国最近承诺合作遏制商业间谍软件滥用之后采取的。</p><p>写信给达斯汀·沃尔兹： <a href="mailto:dustin.volz@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dustin.volz@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 18 Jul 2023 14:37:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/european-spyware-firms-threaten-global-security-and-privacy-us-says-ca86c35f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/european-spyware-firms-threaten-global-security-and-privacy-us-says-ca86c35f<author><![CDATA[Dustin Volz]]></author><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>国际关系</category><category>网络犯罪/黑客攻击</category><category>人权/公民自由</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>唐·格雷夫斯</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>国际关系</category><category>网络犯罪</category><category>黑客攻击</category><category>人权</category><category>公民权利</category><category>政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Pushes Military Cooperation in Space]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>太空作战负责人表示，乌克兰冲突清楚地表明太空对于现代战争至关重要<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001062523"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818859?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">钱斯·萨尔茨曼将军表示，俄罗斯和中国已经在太空领域发展了重要的能力。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：索尔·勒布/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001062523"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/alistair-macdonald" itemprop="url" rel="author">阿利斯泰尔·麦克唐纳</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 18 日上午 5:24 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-pushes-military-cooperation-in-space-6658f974"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>美国促进盟国之间更紧密军事一体化的努力正在延伸到太空。</p><p>太空作战负责人钱斯·萨尔茨曼将军在接受采访时表示，美国军方希望盟国共同训练和规划太空作战，就像他们在地面、空中和海上作战中所做的那样。</p><p>此举之际，人们担心中国和俄罗斯破坏西方卫星以及两国开发的新技术（包括<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pentagon-prepares-for-space-warfare-as-potential-threats-from-china-russia-grow-62a0623b?page=1&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">可以夺取他人的卫星）</a>的能力。例如，俄罗斯已采取行动<a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/russia-ukraine-latest-news-2022-05-10/card/us-u-k-eu-blame-russia-for-cyberattack-on-satellite-provider-P0H489yUmcAQqb1DSnQR?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">破坏乌克兰的太空通信</a>。</p><p>萨尔茨曼说：“乌克兰的冲突清楚地表明：进入和利用太空是现代战争的基础。”他最近与欧洲同行举行了一系列会议，以推动加强合作。</p><p>萨尔茨曼表示，其目标是在盟国之间共享互操作性，并联合训练和开发地面、空中和海上作战部队现有的战术、技术和程序。</p><p> “当你[在盟友之间]整合时，你就处于一个完全不同的位置，而不仅仅是协调，”萨尔茨曼说。</p><p>俄罗斯去年入侵乌克兰，导致北大西洋公约组织成员国和美国其他传统盟友之间在向基辅提供武器和训练方面加强了协调。随着中国在太平洋地区变得更加自信，美国还一直试图与日本和澳大利亚等盟友建立联盟，以对抗中国。</p><p>太空领域已经存在一些军事协调，包括共享卫星发射以及德国和法国的北约太空中心。但萨尔茨曼表示，他认为迄今为止的合作才刚刚起步，需要进一步推进。</p><p> “数量本身就是一种质量，”他说，这句话经常在军队中使用。他补充说，例如，一个大联盟的卫星比一个国家的卫星更难被瞄准。</p><p>萨尔茨曼最近在伦敦郊外的皇家国际航空展上发表讲话时表示，英国、澳大利亚、加拿大、法国和其他盟国的太空专业知识给他留下了深刻的印象。他说，虽然这些国家的预算没有美国那么大，但他们在太空方面的“战略思维”很有价值。</p><p>俄罗斯和中国在太空领域发展了重要的能力。</p><p>萨尔茨曼表示，俄罗斯一直在“不负责任地靠近”其他国家的卫星发射卫星来跟踪它们。莫斯科拥有“嵌套娃娃”卫星，可以释放一个可用于攻击太空中其他物体的物体，而中国则测试了可用于抓取其他卫星的机械臂。两国都展示了可以摧毁轨道卫星的导弹。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=7A968E6A-C5D1-47C5-9A49-CAB374107605&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-s-pushes-military-cooperation-in-space-6658f974&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">中国计划向近地轨道发射数千颗宽带卫星，让全球数亿人上网并销售连接。但这样做将使它与 SpaceX 的 Starlink 竞争。 《华尔街日报》探讨了中国如何在这个拥挤的领域进行竞争。插图：《华尔街日报》的 MacKenzie Coffman、Preston Jessee<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>乌克兰战争开始时，俄罗斯干扰了卫星通信和美国卫星导航系统全球定位系统。</p><p>萨尔茨曼说，美国从中吸取的教训之一是，支持卫星通信的地面资产和太空资产一样需要受到保护。他说，另一个要点是需要无数的商业运营商来增强国家提供商的能力。</p><p> “当这些卫星受到影响时，乌克兰恢复通信的最快方法是通过商业增强，”他说。</p><p>当提供电话和互联网服务的手机信号塔在战争初期被摧毁时， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-leans-on-elon-musks-starlink-in-fight-against-russia-11657963804?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">乌克兰转向埃隆·马斯克的星链服务</a>，该服务使用大量卫星提供互联网连接。</p><p>马斯克旗下的 SpaceX 还<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/elon-musks-spacex-now-has-a-de-facto-monopoly-on-rocket-launches-3c34f02e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">垄断了美国火箭发射市场的大部分市场</a>，这导致业内人士担心其垄断地位。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您认为太空在现代战争中将发挥什么作用？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>萨尔兹曼否认了这些担忧。</p><p>他说：“有很多发射提供商正在迅速竞争，我们所处的空间与 10 年前截然不同。”他指的是美国禁止使用俄罗斯火箭进行发射的例子，这给了他们更少的选择进入太空。</p><p>不过，卫星宇宙的某些部分将不得不留在国家手中。</p><p> “本质上需要执行一些军事职能……你不能将这些职能外包，”他说。</p><p>写信给阿利斯泰尔·麦克唐纳 (Alistair MacDonald)： <a href="mailto:Alistair.Macdonald@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Alistair.Macdonald@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 18 Jul 2023 09:24:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-pushes-military-cooperation-in-space-6658f974</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-pushes-military-cooperation-in-space-6658f974<author><![CDATA[Alistair MacDonald]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>航空航天产品/零件</category><category>卫星</category><category>航空航天/国防</category><category>工业品</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>空间</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>空间</category><category>航空航天产品</category><category>部分</category><category>卫星</category><category>航天</category><category>防御</category><category>工业品</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[People Have Begun to Love Apple’s Most Hated Product]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>蒂姆·库克曾为苹果地图道歉；现在它是一些人的首选导航应用程序<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-812767/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>照片插图：Rachel Mendelson/《华尔街日报》，Apple<span>照片插图：Rachel Mendelson/《华尔街日报》，Apple</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001035418"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001035418"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ann-marie-alcantara"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-629922/AM" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ann-marie-alcantara" itemprop="url" rel="author">安-玛丽·阿尔坎塔拉</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 17 日晚上 9:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/apple-maps-app-popularity-iphone-8e52aec1"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>当你开车去参加聚会时迷路了，有人可能会问：“为什么，你使用了 Apple 地图？”</p><p> 2012 年推出后，<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="">苹果</a><span class="company-name-type">的</span>道路地图应用程序很快就陷入了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10000872396390443890304578008712527187512?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">混乱的境地</a>。大开曼岛缺乏道路。纽约的曼哈顿大桥看起来就像过山车。澳大利亚官员警告称，其一些导航缺陷<a href="https://www.wsj.com/amp/articles/BL-DGB-25669?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">“可能危及生命”。</a></p><p>苹果首席执行官蒂姆·库克罕<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/BL-DGB-25004?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">见地向客户道歉</a>，并<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052970204840504578089102411834238?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">解雇了软件主管</a>。该公司随后花了数年时间试图修复该服务。</p><p>现在，根据客户和用户体验分析师的说法，它已经做到了。一些用户正在寻找改用苹果地图的理由，包括其清晰的公共交通方向和具有视觉吸引力的设计。</p><p>虽然苹果可能不需要这款应用来销售更多 iPhone，但该公司在汽车和增强现实耳机方面的远大抱负取决于人们真正喜欢使用的地图。</p><p> “地图已经取得了长足的进步，人们已经注意到了，”苹果软件主管克雷格·费德里吉 (Craig Federighi) 在该公司 2020 年全球开发者大会上表示。</p><p> Jason Rabinowitz 在推出 Apple 地图后非常愤怒，他转而使用 Android，以便更轻松地使用 Google 地图。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/0444f552-0420-430f-8244-1c2ecf5c0eb8.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>但这并没有持续多久。这位 37 岁的航空业分析师于 2015 年重新使用 iPhone。作为纽约人，他更依赖交通路线而不是驾车路线。几年前，在苹果推出一些新的交通功能后，他尝试了苹果地图，结果让他感到惊讶。</p><p>他现在认为苹果地图比谷歌能更好地提供创意、更快的路线，并更好地管理地铁停运的不可预测性。他向来访的朋友和家人推荐这里。</p><p>拉比诺维茨还喜欢苹果地图更清晰的交通视图，而不是谷歌地图更混乱的设计。</p><p>他称谷歌的传输层“丑陋得令人发指”。但他仍然使用谷歌地图开车。</p><h3>追赶</h3><p>据 Canalys 称，虽然所有 iPhone 上都预装了苹果地图，但美国绝大多数 iPhone 都下载了谷歌地图作为替代方案。为了让人们打开苹果地图，苹果必须采用谷歌地图中已经流行的功能，例如街景功能。苹果在 6 月份的开发者大会上表示，用户将能够离线使用地图，这是谷歌多年来提供的另一项功能。</p><p>但一些视觉效果，例如城市的 3D 天桥视图，首先出现在 Apple 地图中。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/atmospheric/amp.html?guid=02B352E6-1FF8-46D5-83C5-FC0FB3A6AC87" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Apple 地图上的增强现实步行路线利用现实世界来引导人们到达目的地。安-玛丽·阿尔坎塔拉/华尔街日报<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>谷歌地图也不断发展，具有诸如沉浸式 3D 视图等功能，可让您<a href="https://blog.google/products/maps/google-maps-updates-io-2023/" target="_blank" class="icon none">查看一天中不同时间的地点</a>，以及用于查找附近商店、餐馆和其他兴趣点的<a href="https://blog.google/products/maps/new-maps-updates-to-help-you-make-the-most-of-the-holidays/" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">AR 工具</a>。</p><p>苹果地图相对于谷歌的最大竞争优势在于其与 iPhone 的更深入集成。任何需要导航的 iOS 服务（从在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/YELP" class="company-name">Yelp</a>中查找餐馆到在“查找”中查找 AirTags）都使用 Apple 地图。用户无法改变这一点。</p><p>用户体验顾问彼得·拉姆齐（Peter Ramsey）曾撰写过有关苹果地图和谷歌地图之间<a href="https://builtformars.com/case-studies/maps" target="_blank" class="icon none">设计差异的</a>文章，他说：“人们本质上很懒，并且会围绕默认选项养成习惯。” “很长一段时间以来，苹果地图的表现非常糟糕，以至于人们主动转向谷歌地图，但随着苹果地图体验的改善，人们采取打破默认行为的动力越来越少。”</p><h3>风格要点</h3><p>简·纳托利,</p>平时是 Google 地图的高级用户，自从 iPhone 提示她在明尼阿波利斯-圣路易斯使用 Apple 地图后，她发现自己在日常生活中更多地使用了 Apple 地图。保罗国际机场。该应用程序知道她在机场，并为她的航站楼内的商店和餐馆提供建议。这位 42 岁的旧金山政治组织者表示，它比谷歌地图拥有更清晰的信息，更容易互动。 <p></p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="410" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816855?width=700&amp;height=410" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Apple 地图显示机场航站楼内的餐厅和商店。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “这让我重新审视并重新思考我之前对此的一些假设，”纳托利说。 “无论苹果地图最初面临什么声誉障碍，我认为他们已经克服了这些障碍。”</p><p>在机场外，纳托利喜欢苹果的设计，并发现方向更容易阅读，尤其是街道名称。她说，在谷歌地图上，有时无论放大多大，都很难弄清楚街道名称。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您更喜欢苹果地图还是谷歌地图？为什么？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> “谷歌向我展示了餐馆、酒吧和其他东西，但我不一定要寻找这些，”她说。</p><p>最近从佐治亚理工学院毕业的 22 岁女孩 Angelica Nguyen 也有类似的看法。晚上开车时，她发现苹果地图上的道路更容易看清，而且干扰她视野的兴趣点也更少。</p><p> “苹果真的很擅长让东西看起来更漂亮，”Nguyen 说。</p><h3>远非完美</h3><p>在可预见的未来，一些 iPhone 用户仍然会抱怨苹果地图，尤其是当他们觉得地图是强加给他们的时候。</p><p> 23 岁的服装设计专业学生劳拉·普拉兹维奇 (Laura Pladziewicz) 表示，当她在波士顿散步时，她被苹果地图引入了歧途。她在大都会区长大，但不太了解这座城市本身。她遵从苹果地图，因为它是默认地图，而且她承认她没有足够的动力去下载谷歌地图应用程序。</p><p> “尽管它一直让我受委屈，但我已经习惯了伸手去拿它，”她谈到苹果地图时说道。有时，她确实会在手机网络浏览器中的 Google 地图上查找内容。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="418" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-815852?width=700&amp;height=418" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">诺亚·阿卜杜勒阿齐兹 (Noah Abdelaziz) 认为，在 CarPlay 上使用 Apple 地图会导致通勤时间延长。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：诺亚·阿卜杜拉齐兹</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>25 岁的法学院学生诺亚·阿卜杜勒阿齐兹 (Noah Abdelaziz) 今年夏天在洛杉矶租了一辆车往返实习。它拥有Apple的车载平台CarPlay，可让驾驶员通过汽车显示屏使用iPhone应用程序和服务。当 Abdelaziz 连接他的 iPhone 时，它​​会自动在主屏幕上显示 Apple 地图。</p><p>他说，为了避免交通堵塞，苹果地图会带他穿过带有停车标志的住宅区，他认为这会增加他的通勤时间。</p><p>他的实习很快结束了。在使用 CarPlay 近一个半月后，他已经学会了如何在 CarPlay 上使用 Google 地图。</p><p> <em>—欲了解更多《华尔街日报》科技分析、评论、建议和头条新闻，</em> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/newsletters?sub=55&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none"><em>请订阅我们的每周通讯</em></a><em>。</em> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/824b30d1-428f-4e1d-8a3e-62546516565e.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>写信给 Ann-Marie Alcántara，邮箱为<a href="mailto:ann-marie.alcantara@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ann-marie.alcantara@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 18 Jul 2023 01:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/apple-maps-app-popularity-iphone-8e52aec1</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/apple-maps-app-popularity-iphone-8e52aec1<author><![CDATA[Ann-Marie Alcántara]]></author><category> WSJ生活工作</category><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>联网</category><category>汽车电子</category><category>电信设备</category><category>个人电子产品</category><category>机动车零件</category><category>互联网搜索引擎</category><category>汽车</category><category>汽车远程信息处理</category><category>手机/移动电话</category><category>联网汽车技术</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>电子导航/跟踪系统</category><category>卫星导航系统</category><category>移动设备</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>物联网技术</category><category>技术</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>地理/地质学</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>个人技术</category><category>科学/人文</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>苹果</category><category>AAPL</category><category>蒂姆·库克</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>地理</category><category>地质学</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>个人技术</category><category>科学</category><category>人文学科</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>联网</category><category>汽车电子</category><category>电信设备</category><category>个人电子产品</category><category>机动车辆零件</category><category>互联网搜索引擎</category><category>汽车</category><category>汽车远程信息处理</category><category>细胞</category><category>手机</category><category>互联车辆技术</category><category>电子导航</category><category>追踪系统</category><category>卫星导航系统</category><category>移动设备</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>物联网技术</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Silicon Valley Money Men Are Buzzing About Robert F. Kennedy Jr.]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Twitter 联合创始人杰克·多尔西 (Jack Dorsey) 等人赞扬总统候选人<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-815062/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="小罗伯特·F·肯尼迪正在与拜登总统争夺民主党总统提名。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>小罗伯特·F·肯尼迪正在与拜登总统争夺民主党总统提名。苏菲·帕克 (Sophie Park) 为《华尔街日报》<span>拍摄 苏菲·帕克 (Sophie Park) 为《华尔街日报》拍摄</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001045641"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001045641"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/angel-au-yeung" itemprop="url" rel="author">Angel Au-Yeung</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/berber-jin" itemprop="url" rel="author">Berber Jin</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 17 日晚上 9:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/silicon-valley-money-men-are-buzzing-about-robert-f-kennedy-jr-3b5dea5e"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>小罗伯特·F·肯尼迪表示，儿童时期的疫苗与自闭症有关，而且中央情报局杀死了他的叔叔。他曾公开表示想知道接触 Wi-Fi 是否会导致癌症。一些科技界的大明星称赞<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/robert-f-kennedy-election-presidential-campaign-2024-5265d2b8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">他的总统竞选活动</a>。</p><p>硅谷喜欢逆向思维，这就是为什么一些科技名人在 2016 年和 2020 年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/investor-peter-thiel-donald-trump-gets-big-things-right-1477934224?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">支持</a>共和党人<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">唐纳德·特朗普</a>。这一次，民主党人肯尼迪成为科技界反建制言论的焦点。</p><p> Twitter联合创始人杰克·多尔西最近表示支持肯尼迪，后者正在与拜登总统争夺民主党<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/robert-kennedy-jr-files-to-run-for-president-as-a-democrat-1149fd33?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">总统提名</a>。肯尼迪受到了其他一些科技巨头的款待，包括<strong>&nbsp;</strong> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/when-spac-man-chamath-palihapitiya-speaks-reddit-and-wall-street-listen-11615006818?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">SPAC 国王</a>查马斯·帕里哈皮蒂亚 (Chamath Palihapitiya) 和大卫·萨克斯 (David Sacks)，后者是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PYPL" class="company-name">PayPal</a>的创始高管，也是埃隆·马斯克 ( <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/elon-musk">Elon Musk)</a>值得信赖的耳朵。现已关闭的文件共享网站 LimeWire 的创始人马克·戈顿 (Mark Gorton) 成立了一个支持肯尼迪的 PAC。</p><p>他们说他们喜欢他愿意打破现状的态度。</p><p> “先生。肯尼迪的竞选活动是关于未来，而不是过去，”前国会议员、肯尼迪竞选经理丹尼斯·库西尼奇说。 “科技界人士希望总统具有前瞻性，希望扩大美国在科技领域的作用，尊重数据隐私，并且在对待政府的方式上具有深刻的创造力。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-815059?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Twitter 联合创始人杰克·多尔西 (Jack Dorsey) 表达了对小罗伯特·F·肯尼迪 (Robert F. Kennedy Jr.) 的支持。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：科尔·伯斯顿/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>民意调查普遍认为肯尼迪是十几岁的人。 LinkedIn联合创始人里德·霍夫曼和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="company-name">Netflix</a>联合创始人里德·黑斯廷斯等硅谷权力掮客都支持拜登，预计拜登将成为<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-biden-2024-presidential-re-election-campaign-87ef002b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">提名人</a>。</p><p>尽管如此，围绕肯尼迪的关注加上他家族的受欢迎的名字使民主党的初选进程变得复杂化。</p><p>拜登的一名顾问表示：“随着美国人更多地了解他的极端和不受欢迎的记录，他的支持率将继续动摇。”</p><p>据《纽约邮报》首先发表的言论，肯尼迪上周表示，Covid-19 针对的是黑人和白人，而没有放过德系犹太人或华裔。</p><p>他的言论引起了公众的强烈抗议。肯尼迪在一份声明中表示，他被抹黑为反犹太分子。</p><p>科技行业经常被描绘成一个偏爱进步候选人的群体，但情况并非总是如此。</p><p>斯坦福大学商学院政治经济学教授尼尔·马尔霍特拉表示，政府对疫情的反应，包括封锁，是一个转折点，导致一些科技选民在社会问题上变得更加保守。肯尼迪对 Covid-19 疫苗的安全性表示怀疑，并反对封锁。</p><p>事实上，部分美国企业界对两党的领先者<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/wall-street-mobilizes-for-a-presidential-election-reluctantly-49b4b735?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">都不感兴趣</a>——前总统特朗普是共和党提名的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-republican-presidential-rivals-criticism-39d476c5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">领先者</a>——也给了他一个机会。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/30ab478b-b2ff-4466-a46e-bcb8a7800795.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>马尔霍特拉说：“罗伯特·肯尼迪代表了这个替代方案，他既不是拜登，也不是特朗普。” “特朗普还背负着许多人（包括科技创始人）不喜欢的其他包袱。”</p><p>肯尼迪是一名环境律师，他的观点引起了其他民主党人（包括他自己的家人）的愤怒。该社交媒体网站当时表示，他的 Instagram 帐户因“分享有关冠状病毒或疫苗的被揭穿的说法”而于 2021 年被删除。 （他宣布竞选总统后，他的账户就恢复了。）</p><p>对于一些人来说，这使他成为一个更有趣的候选人：来自建制派的人似乎想要推翻它。</p><p>支持拜登的政治策略师库珀·特博 (Cooper Teboe) 表示：“硅谷是建立在‘快速行动、打破常规’的理念之上，而不是‘缓慢地通过一个议院然后再通过下一个议院进行谈判’。”硅谷。但蒂博说，拜登长期的政治经验是他成功的关键。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-815194?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">前国会议员丹尼斯·库西尼奇 (Dennis Kucinich) 介绍小罗伯特·F·肯尼迪 (Robert F. Kennedy Jr.) 参加 4 月份在波士顿正式宣布的总统竞选活动。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：斯科特·艾森/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>一些关注肯尼迪的科技精英已经与其他候选人调情。例如，萨克斯是佛罗里达州州长<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/ron-desantis">罗恩·德桑蒂斯</a>竞选共和党提名的捐助者。他和马斯克一起在推特上参加了德桑蒂斯的竞选<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ron-desantis-trump-successor-president-3e9df9d6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">活动启动</a>仪式。 Palihapitiya, meanwhile, has voiced support in the past for former United Nations ambassador and South Carolina Gov. Nikki Haley, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/nikki-haley-enters-gop-presidential-race-as-first-major-trump-challenger-4f88d0da?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a GOP hopeful</a> .</p><p> “It&#39;s important to celebrate people who raise serious, demanding questions,” Palihapitiya said in an email. “Clearly, the more people hear from RFK, the more they agree with our view that he should be part of the debate going forward.”</p><p> Sacks and Dorsey didn&#39;t respond to requests for comment.</p><p> Dorsey has backed unconventional presidential candidates in the past. 2019 年，他向科技企业家安德鲁·杨 (Andrew Yang) 和前夏威夷国会女议员图尔西·加巴德 (Tulsi Gabbard) 的竞选活动捐款。 They both ran for the Democratic presidential nomination.</p><p> Gorton, the LimeWire founder, created a super PAC called American Values 2024 that, he said, started as an organization focused on combating “pharmaceutical industry corruption.” It now supports Kennedy&#39;s candidacy.</p><p> “It disgusts me that the Democratic Party has become the party of the neocons and the party of big pharma,” Gorton said in an interview. “I think him running to reclaim the Democratic Party from the corrupt interests is noble.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-815197?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A photograph of Robert F. Kennedy Jr. with his uncle Ted Kennedy and his aunt Eunice Kennedy Shriver was shown to the audience before RFK&#39;s speech in Boston.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: BRIAN SNYDER/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> In 1980, Massachusetts Sen. Ted Kennedy —Robert F. Kennedy Jr.&#39;s uncle—unsuccessfully took on Jimmy Carter for the Democratic Party nomination.卡特后来在大选中输给了罗纳德·里根。 Some blamed Ted Kennedy for <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/if-economy-sours-democrats-will-face-a-tough-choice-11566219836?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">splitting the vote</a> .</p><p> Garry South, a Democratic political strategist who worked on Carter&#39;s presidential campaigns, said he doesn&#39;t see Robert F. Kennedy Jr.&#39;s campaign “rising to that level at all.”</p><p> “Teddy was a mainstream liberal Democrat,” South said. “RFK is a nutcase.”</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>What is your outlook for Robert F. Kennedy Jr.&#39;s campaign?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> Last month, Palihapitiya and Sacks co-hosted a fundraiser in affiliation with Common Sense, another group supporting Kennedy. Tickets were $2,000 for the cocktail reception and $10,000 for the dinner.</p><p> The event, held at Sacks&#39;s mansion in San Francisco, was attended by 75 guests, mostly from tech and crypto industries, said Sofia Karstens, an actress and treasurer of Common Sense.</p><p> At 69, Kennedy is about a decade younger than the 80-year-old Biden. Last month, he <a href="https://twitter.com/RobertKennedyJr/status/1673053159172833280" target="_blank" class="icon none">tweeted a video</a> of himself shirtless and doing push-ups in an outdoor gym. “为与拜登总统的辩论做好准备！”他写了。 (The Democratic National Committee has previously said it would support Biden and won&#39;t sponsor any debates.) </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><amp-twitter width="486" height="657" layout="responsive" data-tweetid="1673053159172833280" data-cards="hidden"></amp-twitter></div><p> Samson Mow, a Canadian tech executive, said Kennedy has shown an understanding that decentralized digital currencies such as bitcoin can promote freedom from government restraints. Kennedy spoke at <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/at-bitcoin-conference-no-bears-allowed-46295ad1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the Bitcoin 2023 conference</a> in Miami in May, calling the cryptocurrency a “bulwark against government and corporate expansion.”</p><p> Kennedy&#39;s decision to engage in tech platforms such as Twitter Spaces and podcasts popular in the tech community have also endeared him to some tech leaders, said Chris Lehane, a former Washington Democratic operative under the Clinton administration who now works at crypto investment firm Haun Ventures.</p><p> In early May, Kennedy appeared on a podcast hosted by four Silicon Valley money men, including Sacks and Palihapitiya, and spoke uninterrupted for nearly two hours.</p><p> “I&#39;ve always been antiestablishment,” Palihapitiya said <strong>&nbsp;</strong> toward the end of the podcast. “The idea of tearing down all these institutions of power gives me glee.”</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Eliza Collins contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Angel Au-Yeung at <a href="mailto:angel.au-yeung@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">angel.au-yeung@wsj.com</a> and Berber Jin at <a href="mailto:berber.jin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">berber.jin@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 18 Jul 2023 01:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/silicon-valley-money-men-are-buzzing-about-robert-f-kennedy-jr-3b5dea5e</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/silicon-valley-money-men-are-buzzing-about-robert-f-kennedy-jr-3b5dea5e<author><![CDATA[Angel Au-YeungBerber Jin]]></author><category> wsjfinance</category><category> wsjfinance-ws</category><category> wsjcorp</category><category> Online Service Providers</category><category> Media/Entertainment</category><category> Social Media Platforms/Tools</category><category> Technology</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Health</category><category> Immunizations</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>Medical Treatments/Procedures</category><category>选举</category><category>国家/总统选举</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>小罗伯特·F·肯尼迪</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>health</category><category> immunizations</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>medical treatments</category><category> procedures</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>总统选举</category><category>online service providers</category><category>媒体</category><category>entertainment</category><category> social media platforms</category><category> tools</category><category> technology </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Silicon Valley Money Men Are Buzzing About Robert F. Kennedy Jr.]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Twitter co-founder Jack Dorsey and others are praising presidential candidate <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-815062/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="Robert F. Kennedy Jr. is running against President Biden for the Democratic Party’s presidential nomination." referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Robert F. Kennedy Jr. is running against President Biden for the Democratic Party&#39;s presidential nomination. Sophie Park for The Wall Street Journal <span>Sophie Park for The Wall Street Journal</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001045641"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001045641"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/angel-au-yeung" itemprop="url" rel="author">Angel Au-Yeung</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/berber-jin" itemprop="url" rel="author">Berber Jin</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 17, 2023 9:00 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/silicon-valley-money-men-are-buzzing-about-robert-f-kennedy-jr-3b5dea5e"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> Robert F. Kennedy Jr. says childhood vaccines are linked to autism and that the Central Intelligence Agency killed his uncle. He has wondered out loud whether Wi-Fi exposure leads to cancer. Some of tech&#39;s big stars are praising <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/robert-f-kennedy-election-presidential-campaign-2024-5265d2b8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">his campaign for president</a> .</p><p> Silicon Valley loves a contrarian, which is why some tech luminaries <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/investor-peter-thiel-donald-trump-gets-big-things-right-1477934224?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">threw their support</a> to Republican <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">Donald Trump</a> in 2016 and 2020. This time around, Kennedy, a Democrat, is the one getting the antiestablishment buzz in the tech world.</p><p> Twitter co-founder Jack Dorsey has recently voiced support for Kennedy, who is running against President Biden for the Democratic Party&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/robert-kennedy-jr-files-to-run-for-president-as-a-democrat-1149fd33?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">presidential nomination</a> . Kennedy has been feted by a handful of other tech titans, including <strong>&nbsp;</strong> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/when-spac-man-chamath-palihapitiya-speaks-reddit-and-wall-street-listen-11615006818?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">SPAC king</a> Chamath Palihapitiya and David Sacks, a founding executive of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PYPL" class="company-name">PayPal</a> and trusted ear to <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/elon-musk">Elon Musk</a> .现已关闭的文件共享网站 LimeWire 的创始人马克·戈顿 (Mark Gorton) 成立了一个支持肯尼迪的 PAC。</p><p> They say they like his willingness to go against the status quo.</p><p> “Mr.肯尼迪的竞选活动是关于未来，而不是过去，”前国会议员、肯尼迪竞选经理丹尼斯·库西尼奇说。 “People in the tech community want a president who is forward-looking, who wants to expand America&#39;s role in technology, has respect for data privacy and is profoundly creative in his approach toward government.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-815059?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Twitter co-founder Jack Dorsey has expressed support for Robert F. Kennedy Jr.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Cole Burston/Bloomberg News</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Polls have generally put Kennedy in the teens. Silicon Valley power brokers such as LinkedIn co-founder Reid Hoffman and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="company-name">Netflix</a> co-founder Reed Hastings are backing Biden, who is expected to be <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-biden-2024-presidential-re-election-campaign-87ef002b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the nominee</a> .</p><p> Still, the attention around Kennedy coupled with his family&#39;s popular name are complicating Democrats&#39; primary process.</p><p> “As Americans are exposed to more about his extreme and unpopular record, his support will continue to falter,” said an adviser to Biden.</p><p> Last week, Kennedy said that Covid-19 targets Black and white people while sparing people of Ashkenazi Jewish or Chinese descent, according to remarks first published by The New York Post.</p><p> His remarks drew public outcry. Kennedy said in a statement that he was being smeared as an anti-Semite.</p><p> The tech industry is often painted as a group that favors progressive candidates, but that isn&#39;t always the case.</p><p> The government&#39;s response to the pandemic, including lockdowns, was an inflection point that caused some tech voters to become more conservative on social issues, said Neil Malhotra, a professor of political economy at Stanford University&#39;s business school.肯尼迪对 Covid-19 疫苗的安全性表示怀疑，并反对封锁。</p><p> The fact that parts of corporate America <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/wall-street-mobilizes-for-a-presidential-election-reluctantly-49b4b735?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">are unenthused</a> about the front-runners for both parties—former President Trump is <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-republican-presidential-rivals-criticism-39d476c5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the front-runner</a> for the GOP nomination—has also given him an opening. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/30ab478b-b2ff-4466-a46e-bcb8a7800795.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> “RFK represents this alternative who is neither Biden nor Trump,” Malhotra said. “Trump comes with a lot of other baggage that a lot of people, including tech founders, don&#39;t like.”</p><p> Kennedy, an environmental lawyer, has drawn ire from other Democrats—including his own family—for his views.该社交媒体网站当时表示，他的 Instagram 帐户因“分享有关冠状病毒或疫苗的被揭穿的说法”而于 2021 年被删除。 (His account was reinstated once he announced his presidential bid.)</p><p> For some, that has made him an even more interesting candidate: someone from the establishment who seems to want to tear it down.</p><p> “Silicon Valley was founded on this idea of &#39;move fast, break things&#39; and not &#39;move slow to negotiate through one chamber [of Congress] and then the next,&#39;” said Cooper Teboe, a pro-Biden political strategist who focuses on Silicon Valley.但蒂博说，拜登长期的政治经验是他成功的关键。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-815194?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Former congressman Dennis Kucinich introduced Robert F. Kennedy Jr. for the official announcement of his presidential run in April in Boston.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Scott Eisen/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Some of the tech elites paying attention to Kennedy have flirted with other candidates. Sacks, for example, is a donor to Florida Gov. <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/ron-desantis">Ron DeSantis</a> &#39;s run for the Republican nomination. He, along with Musk, took part in DeSantis&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ron-desantis-trump-successor-president-3e9df9d6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">campaign launch</a> in a live event on Twitter. Palihapitiya, meanwhile, has voiced support in the past for former United Nations ambassador and South Carolina Gov. Nikki Haley, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/nikki-haley-enters-gop-presidential-race-as-first-major-trump-challenger-4f88d0da?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a GOP hopeful</a> .</p><p> “It&#39;s important to celebrate people who raise serious, demanding questions,” Palihapitiya said in an email. “Clearly, the more people hear from RFK, the more they agree with our view that he should be part of the debate going forward.”</p><p> Sacks and Dorsey didn&#39;t respond to requests for comment.</p><p> Dorsey has backed unconventional presidential candidates in the past. 2019 年，他向科技企业家安德鲁·杨 (Andrew Yang) 和前夏威夷国会女议员图尔西·加巴德 (Tulsi Gabbard) 的竞选活动捐款。 They both ran for the Democratic presidential nomination.</p><p> Gorton, the LimeWire founder, created a super PAC called American Values 2024 that, he said, started as an organization focused on combating “pharmaceutical industry corruption.” It now supports Kennedy&#39;s candidacy.</p><p> “It disgusts me that the Democratic Party has become the party of the neocons and the party of big pharma,” Gorton said in an interview. “I think him running to reclaim the Democratic Party from the corrupt interests is noble.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-815197?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> A photograph of Robert F. Kennedy Jr. with his uncle Ted Kennedy and his aunt Eunice Kennedy Shriver was shown to the audience before RFK&#39;s speech in Boston.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: BRIAN SNYDER/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> In 1980, Massachusetts Sen. Ted Kennedy —Robert F. Kennedy Jr.&#39;s uncle—unsuccessfully took on Jimmy Carter for the Democratic Party nomination.卡特后来在大选中输给了罗纳德·里根。 Some blamed Ted Kennedy for <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/if-economy-sours-democrats-will-face-a-tough-choice-11566219836?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">splitting the vote</a> .</p><p> Garry South, a Democratic political strategist who worked on Carter&#39;s presidential campaigns, said he doesn&#39;t see Robert F. Kennedy Jr.&#39;s campaign “rising to that level at all.”</p><p> “Teddy was a mainstream liberal Democrat,” South said. “RFK is a nutcase.”</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>What is your outlook for Robert F. Kennedy Jr.&#39;s campaign?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> Last month, Palihapitiya and Sacks co-hosted a fundraiser in affiliation with Common Sense, another group supporting Kennedy. Tickets were $2,000 for the cocktail reception and $10,000 for the dinner.</p><p> The event, held at Sacks&#39;s mansion in San Francisco, was attended by 75 guests, mostly from tech and crypto industries, said Sofia Karstens, an actress and treasurer of Common Sense.</p><p> At 69, Kennedy is about a decade younger than the 80-year-old Biden. Last month, he <a href="https://twitter.com/RobertKennedyJr/status/1673053159172833280" target="_blank" class="icon none">tweeted a video</a> of himself shirtless and doing push-ups in an outdoor gym. “为与拜登总统的辩论做好准备！”他写了。 (The Democratic National Committee has previously said it would support Biden and won&#39;t sponsor any debates.) </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><amp-twitter width="486" height="657" layout="responsive" data-tweetid="1673053159172833280" data-cards="hidden"></amp-twitter></div><p> Samson Mow, a Canadian tech executive, said Kennedy has shown an understanding that decentralized digital currencies such as bitcoin can promote freedom from government restraints. Kennedy spoke at <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/at-bitcoin-conference-no-bears-allowed-46295ad1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the Bitcoin 2023 conference</a> in Miami in May, calling the cryptocurrency a “bulwark against government and corporate expansion.”</p><p> Kennedy&#39;s decision to engage in tech platforms such as Twitter Spaces and podcasts popular in the tech community have also endeared him to some tech leaders, said Chris Lehane, a former Washington Democratic operative under the Clinton administration who now works at crypto investment firm Haun Ventures.</p><p> In early May, Kennedy appeared on a podcast hosted by four Silicon Valley money men, including Sacks and Palihapitiya, and spoke uninterrupted for nearly two hours.</p><p> “I&#39;ve always been antiestablishment,” Palihapitiya said <strong>&nbsp;</strong> toward the end of the podcast. “The idea of tearing down all these institutions of power gives me glee.”</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Eliza Collins contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Angel Au-Yeung at <a href="mailto:angel.au-yeung@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">angel.au-yeung@wsj.com</a> and Berber Jin at <a href="mailto:berber.jin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">berber.jin@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 18 Jul 2023 01:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/silicon-valley-money-men-are-buzzing-about-robert-f-kennedy-jr-3b5dea5e</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/silicon-valley-money-men-are-buzzing-about-robert-f-kennedy-jr-3b5dea5e<author><![CDATA[Angel Au-YeungBerber Jin]]></author><category> wsjfinance</category><category> wsjfinance-ws</category><category> wsjcorp</category><category> Online Service Providers</category><category> Media/Entertainment</category><category> Social Media Platforms/Tools</category><category> Technology</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Health</category><category> Immunizations</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>Medical Treatments/Procedures</category><category>选举</category><category>国家/总统选举</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>小罗伯特·F·肯尼迪</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>health</category><category> immunizations</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>medical treatments</category><category> procedures</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>总统选举</category><category>online service providers</category><category>媒体</category><category>entertainment</category><category> social media platforms</category><category> tools</category><category> technology </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[People Have Begun to Love Apple’s Most Hated Product]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Tim Cook once apologized for Apple Maps; now it is the preferred navigation app for some <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-812767/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Photo illustration by Rachel Mendelson/The Wall Street Journal, Apple <span>Photo illustration by Rachel Mendelson/The Wall Street Journal, Apple</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001035418"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001035418"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ann-marie-alcantara"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-629922/AM" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ann-marie-alcantara" itemprop="url" rel="author">Ann-Marie Alcántara</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 17, 2023 9:00 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/apple-maps-app-popularity-iphone-8e52aec1"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> You get lost driving to a party and there is a chance someone will ask, “Why, did you use Apple Maps?”</p><p> After its 2012 launch, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="">Apple</a> <span class="company-name-type">&#39;s</span> road-atlas app quickly routed itself into <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10000872396390443890304578008712527187512?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">hot-mess territory</a> .大开曼岛缺乏道路。纽约的曼哈顿大桥看起来就像过山车。 Officials in Australia warned that some of its navigation flaws <a href="https://www.wsj.com/amp/articles/BL-DGB-25669?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">were “potentially life threatening.”</a></p><p> Apple CEO Tim Cook issued <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/BL-DGB-25004?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a rare apology</a> to customers and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052970204840504578089102411834238?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">fired his head of software</a> .该公司随后花了数年时间试图修复该服务。</p><p> Now, according to customers and user-experience analysts, it has. Some users are finding reasons to switch to Apple Maps, including its clear public transit directions and its visually appealing design.</p><p> While Apple might not need the app to sell any more iPhones, the company&#39;s lofty ambitions with cars and augmented-reality headsets depend on maps people actually like using.</p><p> “Maps has come a long way, and people have noticed,” Craig Federighi, Apple&#39;s head of software, said during the company&#39;s 2020 Worldwide Developers Conference.</p><p> Jason Rabinowitz was so incensed after the introduction of Apple Maps he switched to Android, to more easily use Google Maps. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/0444f552-0420-430f-8244-1c2ecf5c0eb8.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> That didn&#39;t last.这位 37 岁的航空业分析师于 2015 年重新使用 iPhone。作为纽约人，他更依赖交通路线而不是驾车路线。 A few years ago, after Apple promoted some new transit features, he gave Apple Maps a try and the results surprised him.</p><p> He now thinks Apple Maps suggests creative, faster routes and manages the unpredictability of subway outages better than Google does. He recommends it to friends and family who visit.</p><p> Rabinowitz also likes Apple Maps&#39; cleaner transit view versus the more cluttered design of Google Maps.</p><p> He calls Google&#39;s transit layer “sinfully ugly to look at.” But he does still use Google Maps for driving.</p><h3> Playing catch-up</h3><p> While Apple Maps comes preinstalled on all iPhones, the overwhelming majority of iPhones in the US have Google Maps downloaded as an alternative, according to Canalys.为了让人们打开苹果地图，苹果必须采用谷歌地图中已经流行的功能，例如街景功能。 Apple said at its developer conference in June that users would be able to use maps offline, another feature Google has offered for years.</p><p> But some visual effects, such as 3-D flyover views of cities, first appeared in Apple Maps. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/atmospheric/amp.html?guid=02B352E6-1FF8-46D5-83C5-FC0FB3A6AC87" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Augmented-reality walking directions on Apple Maps use the real world to guide people to their destinations. ANN-MARIE ALCÁNTARA/THE WALL STREET JOURNAL<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Google Maps has also evolved, with features such as an immersive 3-D view that lets you <a href="https://blog.google/products/maps/google-maps-updates-io-2023/" target="_blank" class="icon none">check what places look like</a> at different times of day, and <a href="https://blog.google/products/maps/new-maps-updates-to-help-you-make-the-most-of-the-holidays/" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">an AR tool</a> for finding nearby shops, restaurants and other points of interest.</p><p> The biggest competitive advantage Apple Maps has over Google is its deeper integration in the iPhone. Any iOS service that requires directions—from finding restaurants in <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/YELP" class="company-name">Yelp</a> to locating AirTags in Find My—uses Apple Maps. Users can&#39;t change that.</p><p> “People are inherently lazy and form habits around default options,” says Peter Ramsey, a user-experience consultant who has written about <a href="https://builtformars.com/case-studies/maps" target="_blank" class="icon none">design differences</a> between Apple and Google Maps. “For a long time Apple Maps was so bad that people proactively switched to Google Maps, but as the experience of Apple Maps improved, there was less incentive to make that default-breaking action.”</p><h3> Style points</h3><p> Jane Natoli,</p> normally a Google Maps power user, finds herself using Apple Maps more in her everyday life after her iPhone prompted her to use it in the Minneapolis-St. Paul International Airport. The app knew she was at the airport and offered recommendations for shops and restaurants in her terminal. It had clearer information that was easier to interact with than Google Maps, says the 42-year-old San Francisco-based political organizer. <p></p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="410" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816855?width=700&amp;height=410" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Apple Maps displays restaurants and shops in airport terminals.</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “It made me kind of revisit and rethink some of my prior assumptions about it,” Natoli says. “Whatever initial reputational hurdles that Apple Maps faced, I think they&#39;ve jumped over those.”</p><p> Outside the airport, Natoli likes Apple&#39;s design and finds directions easier to read, especially street names. On Google Maps sometimes it&#39;s difficult to figure out the street name, no matter how closely you zoom in, she says.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>Do you prefer Apple Maps or Google Maps? Why?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> “Google is showing me restaurants, bars and other things, but I&#39;m not necessarily looking for that,” she says.</p><p> Angelica Nguyen, a 22-year-old who recently graduated from Georgia Tech, shares a similar sentiment. At night while driving, she finds that the roads are easier to look at on Apple Maps, and there are fewer points of interest cluttering her view.</p><p> “Apple&#39;s really good at making things look pretty,” Nguyen says.</p><h3> Far from perfect</h3><p> Some iPhone users will still grumble about Apple Maps for the foreseeable future—especially when they feel like it is being pushed on them.</p><p> Laura Pladziewicz, a 23-year-old costume-design student, says she has been led astray by Apple Maps as she walks around Boston.她在大都会区长大，但不太了解这座城市本身。她遵从苹果地图，因为它是默认地图，而且她承认她没有足够的动力去下载谷歌地图应用程序。</p><p> “Even though it keeps wronging me, I&#39;m used to reaching for that,” she says of Apple Maps. She does, on occasion, look up stuff on Google Maps in her phone&#39;s web browser. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="418" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-815852?width=700&amp;height=418" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Noah Abdelaziz felt that using Apple Maps on CarPlay led to a longer commute.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Noah Abdelaziz</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Noah Abdelaziz, a 25-year-old law student, rented a car in Los Angeles this summer to get to and from his internship.它拥有Apple的车载平台CarPlay，可让驾驶员通过汽车显示屏使用iPhone应用程序和服务。 When Abdelaziz connected his iPhone, it automatically displayed Apple Maps on the home screen.</p><p> To avoid gridlock, he says Apple Maps would take him through residential neighborhoods with stop signs, which he believes added time to his commute.</p><p> His internship ends soon. After almost a month and a half on CarPlay, he has discovered how to use Google Maps on it.</p><p> <em>—For more WSJ Technology analysis, reviews, advice and headlines,</em> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/newsletters?sub=55&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none"><em>sign up for our weekly newsletter</em></a> <em>.</em> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/824b30d1-428f-4e1d-8a3e-62546516565e.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Write to Ann-Marie Alcántara at <a href="mailto:ann-marie.alcantara@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ann-marie.alcantara@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 18 Jul 2023 01:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/apple-maps-app-popularity-iphone-8e52aec1</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/apple-maps-app-popularity-iphone-8e52aec1<author><![CDATA[Ann-Marie Alcántara]]></author><category> wsjlifework</category><category> Computers/Consumer Electronics</category><category> Networking</category><category> Automobile Electronics</category><category> Telecommunications Equipment</category><category> Personal Electronics</category><category> Motor Vehicle Parts</category><category> Internet Search Engines</category><category> Automotive</category><category> Automotive Telematics</category><category> Cell/Mobile Phones</category><category> Connected Vehicle Technologies</category><category> Consumer Electronics</category><category> Electronic Navigation/Tracking Systems</category><category> Satellite Navigation Systems</category><category> Mobile Devices</category><category> Industrial Electronics</category><category>工业品</category><category>Online Service Providers</category><category> Internet-of-Things Technologies</category><category> Technology</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Geography/Geology</category><category> Living/Lifestyle</category><category> Personal Technology</category><category> Sciences/Humanities</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Apple</category><category> AAPL</category><category> Tim Cook</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>geograph